Cloud shell is an interactive, browser- accesible shell for managing Azure Resources 

Azure cloud shell
Cli commands - 
az group list - This will show all the resource groups of your subscription

To create vm 
az vm create `
--resource-group "<RG_NAME>" `
--name LabVM `
--image debian11 `
--size Standard_B1ms `
--admin-username azureuser `
--generate-ssh-keys `
--public-ip-sku Standard

To Remove a VM using Powershell
Remove-AzVM -Name "<name>" -ResourceGroupName "<RG_NAME>"

ARM Templates
Arm templates are used to manage resources 

